Document: class_worldenvironment  
Path: godot/classes/class_worldenvironment.rst  
Summary: Configures the default Environment for a scene, managing lighting, post-processing, and background settings.  

The WorldEnvironment node defines the default Environment for the scene. Parameters set here can be overridden by an Environment node attached to the current Camera3D. Only one WorldEnvironment instance may exist in a scene at a time. This node specifies default lighting parameters such as ambient lighting, enables post-processing effects like SSAO, DOF, and Tonemapping, and determines background rendering options (solid color, skybox). These settings are typically used to enhance scene realism and color balance.
